---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Policy"
  description="Read the Blindsided Games privacy and data handling policy for website and game services, including analytics, advertising, and contact submissions."
  path="/policy"
>
  <section class="section" data-reveal>
    <div class="container section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Policy</p>
      <h1>Privacy and Data Handling</h1>
      <p>Last updated: March 5, 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" data-reveal>
    <div class="container policy-stack">
      <article class="panel">
        <h2>1. Scope</h2>
        <p>
          This policy applies to blindsidedgames.com, official Blindsided Games communications, and game services
          published under Blindsided Games branding unless a platform-specific policy states otherwise.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>2. Information Collected</h2>
        <p>Blindsided Games minimizes collection and does not request sensitive personal identity data by default.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Technical data such as browser type, approximate region, and device diagnostics for reliability.</li>
          <li>Gameplay or product interaction telemetry used to improve balance and feature prioritization.</li>
          <li>Advertising identifiers only where platform consent and regional law permit that behavior.</li>
          <li>Contact form content that you intentionally submit for support or business communication.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>3. How Data Is Used</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Operate and secure websites, game experiences, and platform integrations.</li>
          <li>Diagnose service incidents, regressions, and abuse attempts.</li>
          <li>Respond to player support requests and partnership enquiries.</li>
          <li>Measure product quality and release performance at an aggregate level.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>4. Advertising and Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Some releases may include analytics or ad network tooling. These providers may process device-level
          identifiers under their own terms. Consent prompts and OS privacy controls determine availability where
          required.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>5. Retention and Security</h2>
        <p>
          Data is retained only as long as required for support resolution, legal compliance, and product quality
          operations. Reasonable technical safeguards are applied, including access controls and transport security.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>6. Your Choices</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Use platform controls to reset or restrict ad identifiers.</li>
          <li>Disable optional analytics or ad tracking features where available.</li>
          <li>Request support help directly through Discord or email.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="panel">
        <h2>7. Contact and Requests</h2>
        <p>
          For policy questions, access requests, or corrections, contact
          <a href="mailto:support@blindsidedgames.com">support@blindsidedgames.com</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
